de.interactive_instruments.etf.testdriver

Class TaskPoolRegistry<R,T extends Task<R>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.interactive_instruments.etf.testdriver.TaskPoolRegistry<R,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - generic future result type

    public class TaskPoolRegistry<R,T extends Task<R>>
extends java.lang.Object
    A client can call the pool and create a new task which implements the TaskProgressInterface. The pool will return a Future to the Client, that might be used for calling the result (Future.get() will block and waits for the task to complete). The TaskProgressInterface is used by a client to monitor the progress of the Thread without blocking it.
    See Also:
    Task

      • TaskPoolRegistry

        public TaskPoolRegistry(int corePoolSize,
                        int maxPoolSize,
                        int maxQueueSize)
        Creates a new Task Pool Registry which queues and executes all Tasks If the queue is full, and the number of threads is greater than or equal to maxPoolSize, the task is rejected with an RejectedExecutionException
        Parameters:
        corePoolSize - the number of threads to keep in the pool, even if they are idle for 30 seconds
        maxPoolSize - the maximum number of threads to allow in the pool
        maxQueueSize - the maximum number of queued threads
        Since:
        1.1.0

      • TaskPoolRegistry

        @Deprecated
public TaskPoolRegistry(int corePoolSize,
                                    int maxPoolSize)
        Deprecated. 
        Deprecated, use TaskPoolRegistry(int, int, int) to set the max queue size explicitly. If the internal queue is full, and the number of threads is greater than or equal to maxPoolSize, the task is rejected with an RejectedExecutionException Note: since version 1.1.0, the internal queue size is three times the maxPool size. Before the queue size was equal to the maxPool size
        Parameters:
        corePoolSize - the number of threads to keep in the pool, even if they are idle for 30 seconds
        maxPoolSize - the maximum number of threads to allow in the pool
        Since:
        1.0.0
